SSC Food Service: FYI, For those who registered, the Grab-n-Go pickup will Monday Night, 6:00pm-7:00pm.

REMINDER:
The USDA now requires that we "serve" lunches as if the students are in the building. As a result, students must pay for their lunch at their current status, meaning PAID, REDUCED, or FREE.

While we are remote learning, we will be packaging (5) lunches for distribution for those who respond to the weekly survey. The lunches will be distributed for those students who are registered at Shenandoah for the current school year. We will then charge the students' lunch account for these meals.

Please deposit monies in to your student's account for this service. We are unable to accept payment at the time of pickup but are happy to accept payments online, via mail, or drop off a payment (with STUDENT NAME) at any building during regular office hours. Be aware if you registered and don't pickup, your students account will still be charged. Thank you!

post_text:
SMS Sports start Monday!
Football: Equipment pick up at Door 6, 1:30-3:30. Practice 3:30-5:30.
Volleyball: Practice 4-6pm, Enter at Door 6
Cheerleading Tryouts: 3-5pm, SMS wrestling room. Enter at Door 7
Info on Cross Country and Tennis coming later today.

All athletes need to wear a mask upon entering the school. 1 parent must accompany the athlete to sign a waiver. All athletes must have their own water bottle as the water fountains are shut off.

If the athlete is experiencing Covid symptoms, he/she are not to come to practice and need to contact the coach.

Last year's physicals are acceptable unless your son/daughter had a concussion or surgery. If so, a new physical is needed. Also, parents will need to complete the physical questionnaire before the athlete can participate. Copies are available in the middle school office and will be available at all tryouts.

Any questions, please contact Mrs. Helman at bhelman@shenandoah.k12.in.us

You are welcome to join the parade or just wave as the parade rolls by. Hope to see you all there!

post_text:
This is Greg Allen, Principal at SHS,
I regret to inform our Seniors, staff members, and parents that we will be changing our graduation format for Friday, July 10, 2020. This is necessary due to Governor Holcomb’s decision to keep Indiana at Stage 4.5 instead of going to Stage 5 of his “Back On Track” plan for Indiana. As a result, SHS will no longer be allowed to hold a traditional graduation service. Therefore, SHS will distribute diplomas at 10 AM on Friday, July 10th at Door # 5. Students and Parents will pull up to door 5 and exit their vehicle and will receive their diplomas outside door #5. Students will wear caps and gowns and will have the opportunity to have pictures at this time. Additionally, we are planning a Senior parade through campus and into Middletown at 6:00 PM. I will send out more details later this week. Shenandoah’s administration, school board and staff are very sorry that this change has to be made, but this is for the protection of all involved.

post_text: I am pleased to announce Shenandoah High School will reschedule our graduation ceremonies for the class of 2020 due to the Covid-19 pandemic. The new date for our graduation will be Friday, July 10, 2020 at 6:00 PM. Please understand that these are unprecedented circumstances and we will continue to monitor the feasibility of holding graduation on July 10th. Should this date not be feasible, then we will distribute diplomas to our graduating Seniors in an alternative manner. It is my sincere hope that each graduating Senior will experience a traditional graduation ceremony. I will send out more updates regarding our venue, social distancing, and other limitations that may be placed upon SHS by federal, state, and local mandates. - Greg Allen

Seniors: Please see the memo below from Ivy Tech. Mr. Allen
Senior Student Memo

Congratulations to the Class of 2020! We are proud of all that you have accomplished as you wrap up your senior year of high school. As you prepare for the next step in your educational or career journey, Ivy Tech Community College would like to connect with you to discuss your post-secondary plans (college, career, or enlistment). This conversation will help us in determining how we might best support you. Whether you’ve taken dual credits or not, we would appreciate the chance to chat. If you have taken dual credits with the College, we can discuss how to ensure that your college credits successfully transfer to your college of choice. Sign up for a time here: REGISTRATION/SIGN-UP LINK.

Please let me know if you have any questions about this opportunity for seniors.

Best regards,

Bonnie

Bonnie Willy
Ivy Tech Community College- Muncie-Henry County
George & Frances Ball Building
125 S High Street
Muncie, Indiana 47305

Shenandoah HS Counseling Dept
April 15 at 2:06 PM ·

Attn Students! Below is an update from the College Board regarding SAT tests for the rest of the calendar year.

"The College Board will not be able to administer the SAT and SAT Subject Tests as planned on June 6, 2020.

Students will have opportunities to take the SAT to make up for this spring’s lost administrations. If it’s safe from a public health standpoint, we will provide weekend SAT administrations every month through the end of the calendar year, beginning in August. This includes a new administration in September and the previously scheduled tests on August 29, October 3, November 7, and December 5.

Students will be able to register for these administrations beginning in May. We’ll communicate directly with students when the exact date is available. Eligible students will be able to take the exam with a fee waiver. Students who were registered for June and those in the high school class of 2021 who do not have SAT scores will have early access to registration for the August, September, and October administrations."

Students who were registered for June and those in the high school class of 2021 who do not have SAT scores will have early access to registration for the August, September, and October administrations."
text:
Attn Students! Below is an update from the College Board regarding SAT tests for the rest of the calendar year.

"The College Board will not be able to administer the SAT and SAT Subject Tests as planned on June 6, 2020.

Students will have opportunities to take the SAT to make up for this spring’s lost administrations. If it’s safe from a public health standpoint, we will provide weekend SAT administrations every month through the end of the calendar year, beginning in August. This includes a new administration in September and the previously scheduled tests on August 29, October 3, November 7, and December 5.

Students will be able to register for these administrations beginning in May. We’ll communicate directly with students when the exact date is available. Eligible students will be able to take the exam with a fee waiver. Students who were registered for June and those in the high school class of 2021 who do not have SAT scores will have early access to registration for the August, September, and October administrations."

post_text:
IMPORTANT FINANCIAL AID UPDATE
FAFSA Filing 4/15/20
Although the federal deadline to file taxes has been moved to June the Indiana deadline to file the FAFSA form remains April 15th HOWEVER:
Students who fail to file the FAFSA by the April 15th deadline as a direct result of COVID-19 illness or disruption may submit an appeal to the Indiana Commission for Higher Education using their ScholarTrack account to waive the April 15th deadline. Students will need to explain in their appeal how they were unable to submit the FAFSA by the April 15th deadline either due to a lack of ac-cess to the application, or as a result of serious illness of the student or an immediate family member (student’s spouse, child, parent, guardian, grandparent or sibling).

post_text:
SHS News: CALLING ALL FANS! The SHS Cheerleaders will be participating in the MEC (our conference) Cheer Competition next Wednesday, March 11 at 6:00pm at Daleville High School. The girls have been working all year on perfecting our routine, and unlike any other sports, they only get one 2 minute chance to do a perfect routine.

Crowd participation is a big part of our score, so we would love to see lots of you there! We have placed second the past two years with Daleville winning and they have had a massive crowd cheering them on. So we need lots of fans in the stands.

Thanks for your love and support and we hope to see you next Wednesday!
